SECTION 5. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 63-6-204(g)(1), is amended by
deleting the language "other than radiologists, anesthesiologists, pathologists or emergency
physicians".
SECTION 6. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 63-6-204(h)(5)(A), is amended by
deleting the language "specialties of ophthalmology, pathology, anesthesiology and/or
emergency medicine" and substituting "specialty of ophthalmology".
SECTION 7. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 63-6-204, is amended by adding the
following as a new subsection:
( ) This section does not require a particular employment relationship for the
employment of a radiologist, anesthesiologist, pathologist, or emergency physician, as
long as the employment of such physician otherwise complies with this chapter. As
used in this subsection ( ), "employment relationship" includes employment by direct
means and employment through an agreement with a third party.
SECTION 8. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 63-9-104(f)(3), is amended by
deleting the subdivision.
SECTION 9. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 68-11-205, is amended by deleting
subdivisions (b)(6), (b)(9), (c)(6), (e)(2), (e)(3), (e)(6), (e)(8), and (e)(9), and subsection (g).
SECTION 10. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 68-11-205(b)(1), is amended by
deleting the language ", other than radiologists, anesthesiologists, pathologists, or emergency
physicians,".
SECTION 11. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 68-11-205(c)(1), is amended by
deleting the language ", other than radiologists, anesthesiologists, pathologists or emergency
physicians".
SECTION 12. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 68-11-205, is amended by adding
the following as a new subsection:
- 2 - 000597

( ) This section does not require a particular employment relationship for the
employment of a radiologist, anesthesiologist, pathologist, or emergency physician by a
hospital licensed under this chapter or an affiliate of a hospital, as long as the
employment of such physician otherwise complies with this part. As used in this
subsection ( ), "employment relationship" includes employment by direct means and
employment through an agreement with a third party.
SECTION 13. This act takes effect July 1, 2025, the public welfare requiring it.
